                <note rend="inline" type="source">714.1515/982: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hawks</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-11-28T10:00:00-06:00"
                            >November 28, 1929—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 5:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>154. Referring to the Department’s telegram of November 27, 2 p.m.<note n="45"
                        xml:id="d819fn45">Not printed; it requested the Chargé to inquire whether it
                        would be satisfactory to the Guatemalan Government to have the delegates
                        meet at Washington on January 15, 1930. (714.1515/973)</note> The Minister
                    for Foreign Affairs still maintains the position that unless the Government of
                    Honduras makes the same clear cut statement without any reservations, as has
                    already been made by the Guatemalan Government, to the effect that its delegate
                    will be able to discuss all phases of the problem it will be useless to hold the
                    conference.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Honduras.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hawks</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
